Plants of the Etowah River Basin of Georgia
Dawson County

Diapensiaceae
*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummit
Galax

-Dawson Forest Wildlife Management Area, Amicalola Tract. Two narrow, east-west facing promontories, west side of Amicalola R., 1.1 miles south of State Hwy. 53 Amicalola bridge.

Growing in scattered clumps along base of west-facing slope above Amicalola floodplain, south side of promontory. Below *Rhododendron maximum*. Oak-pine-hickory forest.

(handwritten)
